cs.EM, cs.SE, cs.SY, cs.PL, cs.LO

Reasoning: 
- cs.EM (Embedded Systems) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on modeling and analysis of non-functional properties in automotive real-time embedded systems.
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is also likely as the paper discusses the use of a domain specific language for safety-critical system design.
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is relevant as the paper deals with timing constraints in real-time systems.
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is relevant as the paper introduces a probabilistic extension to a clock constraint specification language.
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is relevant as the paper uses formal verification techniques to prove the correctness of the specification.
